---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Colophon · uxward">
  <style>
    .top { padding-top: var(--space-8); padding-bottom: var(--space-6); }
    .top a.back { font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); text-decoration: none; }
    .top a.back:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .title-block { padding-top: var(--space-7); padding-bottom: var(--space-10); }
    .title-eyebrow { font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-7); }
    h1.title { font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(48px, 6.4vw, 96px); line-height: 0.96; letter-spacing: -0.04em; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }
    h1.title em { font-style: normal; }
    .opening { font-weight: 400; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); max-width: 64ch; margin: var(--space-7) 0 0; }

    .section { padding: var(--space-10) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .section-eyebrow { font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
    .section-head { font-weight: 900; font-size: clamp(30px, 3.6vw, 44px); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 var(--space-9) 0; max-width: 20ch; }
    .section-head em { font-style: normal; }

    .spec { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .spec-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr 280px; gap: var(--space-7); padding: var(--space-6) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: baseline; }
    .spec-row .key { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); }
    .spec-row .name { font-weight: 800; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--ink); letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
    .spec-row .name.mono { font-weight: 700; font-size: 22px; }
    .spec-row .name .why { display: block; font-weight: 400; font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); margin-top: var(--space-3); max-width: 520px; }
    .spec-row a.src { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; text-align: right; min-width: 0; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .spec-row a.src:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .color-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .color-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 80px 200px 1fr 120px; gap: var(--space-7); padding: var(--space-5) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: center; }
    .swatch { width: 56px; height: 56px; border: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .color-row .token-name { font-weight: 800; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.2; color: var(--ink); letter-spacing: -0.015em; }
    .color-row .role { font-weight: 400; font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); max-width: 480px; }
    .color-row .hex { font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--tertiary); text-align: right; }

    .build-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); }
    .build-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr 280px; gap: var(--space-7); padding: var(--space-5) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); align-items: baseline; }
    .build-row .key { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); }
    .build-row .what { font-weight: 500; font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--ink); }
    .build-row .what em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--body); }
    .build-row a.src { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; text-align: right; min-width: 0; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .build-row a.src:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .ack-prose p { font-weight: 400; font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--body); max-width: 660px; margin: 0 0 var(--space-6); }
    .ack-prose p strong { font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); }
    .ack-prose p em { font-style: italic; }
    .ack-prose a { color: var(--ink); }
    .ack-prose a:hover { color: var(--signature); }

    .stamp-row { padding: var(--space-9) 0 var(--space-10); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint); display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--space-7); flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .stamp-row .stamp { font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); }
    .stamp-row .fleuron { font-size: 22px; color: var(--tertiary); }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .spec-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .spec-row a.src { text-align: left; }
      .color-row { grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr; }
      .color-row .role { display: none; }
      .build-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .build-row a.src { text-align: left; }
    }

    /* Cyber easter egg — the colophon documents a different system once the
       override fires. The .cyber class on <html> swaps which version shows. */
    .cyber-only { display: none; }
    :global(.cyber) .normal-only { display: none; }
    :global(.cyber) .cyber-only { display: block; }
    :global(.cyber) .title-block h1.title {
      font-family: var(--cf-head);
      font-variation-settings: normal;
      letter-spacing: 0;
      font-size: clamp(34px, 4.6vw, 64px);
      line-height: 1.15;
      text-shadow: 0 0 6px #19F0FF, 0 0 16px rgba(255, 43, 214, 0.6);
    }
    :global(.cyber) .title-block h1.title em { font-variation-settings: normal; }
  </style>

  <div class="container top">
    <div><a class="back" href="/">Back home</a></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container title-block">
    <div class="normal-only">
      <div class="title-eyebrow">Colophon · How this was made</div>
      <h1 class="title">A note on the <em>making.</em></h1>
      <p class="opening">
        uxward.com is a working journal of Brandon E. B. Ward — designed in light and dark,
        built with restraint, set in one grotesque, and revised quarterly. Most visitors will
        never see this page. If you're reading it, hello. You're the right kind of reader.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="cyber-only">
      <div class="title-eyebrow">Colophon · Override engaged</div>
      <h1 class="title">A note on the <em>breach.</em></h1>
      <p class="opening">
        You found the override. The same working journal, jacked into Night City — wet
        asphalt, fluorescent signage, and a handbrush face pulled off the shelf for the
        occasion. Type the code again, or press Esc, to surface back into daylight.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Typography</div>
      <div class="normal-only">
        <h2 class="section-head">One face, used <em>without apology.</em></h2>
        <div class="spec">
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="key">Everything</span>
            <span class="name">
              Archivo
              <span class="why">A grotesque by Omnibus Type. One face carries the whole site — display, body, labels, numerals alike. The serif-and-mono pairing that used to live here is retired; the page speaks in a single voice now.</span>
            </span>
            <a class="src" href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Archivo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Omnibus Type</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cyber-only">
        <h2 class="section-head">One face becomes <em>two, after dark.</em></h2>
        <div class="spec">
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="key">Override display</span>
            <span class="name">
              Rock Salt
              <span class="why">A weathered handbrush face by Sideshow. It sleeps until a code wakes it, then tags the wordmark and the headlines — graffiti on wet concrete. Unreadable by the paragraph, which is the point: it only ever shouts.</span>
            </span>
            <a class="src" href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Rock+Salt" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sideshow</a>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="key">Everything legible</span>
            <span class="name mono">
              JetBrains Mono
              <span class="why">Carries the body text in Night City, because handpainted letters don't survive real reading. Archivo rests until you surface.</span>
            </span>
            <a class="src" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/lp/mono/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">JetBrains</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Color</div>
      <div class="normal-only">
        <h2 class="section-head">Five tokens. <em>One of them does the talking.</em></h2>
        <div class="color-list">
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #E7E7E7;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Canvas</div>
            <div class="role">The page. A soft off-white — deliberately never pure white.</div>
            <div class="hex">#E7E7E7</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #FAF8F4;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Paper</div>
            <div class="role">A tinted surface for the few framed and inset moments.</div>
            <div class="hex">#FAF8F4</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #040404;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Ink</div>
            <div class="role">The headlines, the wordmark, the body. Near-black — never pure black either.</div>
            <div class="hex">#040404</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #6B6B6B;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Tertiary</div>
            <div class="role">The labels, the timestamps, the faint 10% rules. Quiet by design.</div>
            <div class="hex">#6B6B6B</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #CC0006;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Signature red</div>
            <div class="role">Used with nerve — the section numbers, the contact field, every link's hover. One color that doesn't ask permission.</div>
            <div class="hex">#CC0006</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cyber-only">
        <h2 class="section-head">More tokens, <em>and none of them rationed.</em></h2>
        <div class="color-list">
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #07060F;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Canvas</div>
            <div class="role">Near-black with a bruise of violet. The wet asphalt the whole city reflects off of.</div>
            <div class="hex">#07060F</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #0E0B1D;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Paper</div>
            <div class="role">The lifted panel — one notch off the void, where the callouts sit.</div>
            <div class="hex">#0E0B1D</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #F6F7FF;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Ink</div>
            <div class="role">The text, haloed in cyan. White that refuses to sit still.</div>
            <div class="hex">#F6F7FF</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #FF2BD6;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Neon pink</div>
            <div class="role">The signature, off its leash. Every sign in the city is lit; this one most of all.</div>
            <div class="hex">#FF2BD6</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #19F0FF;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Neon cyan</div>
            <div class="role">The glow under everything — reflections, selection, the hum off the wires.</div>
            <div class="hex">#19F0FF</div>
          </div>
          <div class="color-row">
            <div class="swatch" style="background: #2B6BFF;"></div>
            <div class="token-name">Neon blue</div>
            <div class="role">The deep end of the palette. Rain, distance, the light two blocks down.</div>
            <div class="hex">#2B6BFF</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Build</div>
      <h2 class="section-head">The stack, <em>told briefly.</em></h2>
      <div class="build-list">
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="key">Framework</span>
          <span class="what">Astro — <em>static-first, content-shaped, the right tool for a journal.</em></span>
          <a class="src" href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">astro.build</a>
        </div>
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="key">Hosting</span>
          <span class="what">IONOS. <em>Hosted my first webpage with 1and1.com in Y2K, been here ever since.</em></span>
          <a class="src" href="https://www.ionos.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ionos.com</a>
        </div>
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="key">Content</span>
          <span class="what">HTML — <em>essays and case studies hand-authored in plain, portable markup I'll still be able to read in 2046.</em></span>
          <a class="src" href="https://html.spec.whatwg.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">html.spec.whatwg.org</a>
        </div>
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="key">Domain</span>
          <span class="what">uxward.com — <em>registered 2020, used in earnest 2026.</em></span>
          <span class="src"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="build-row">
          <span class="key">Source</span>
          <span class="what">Public on GitHub. <em>The site itself is part of the work.</em></span>
          <a class="src" href="https://github.com/uxward/uxward" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/uxward/uxward</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">✦ Informed by</div>
      <h2 class="section-head">Borrowed, <em>with thanks.</em></h2>
      <div class="ack-prose">
        <p>
          The systematic backbone of this site is borrowed from <strong>Wim Crouwel</strong> —
          the page as a visible grid, structure you can see rather than hide. The conviction to
          run on a single typeface comes from <strong>Experimental Jetset</strong>: one grotesque,
          used without apology. The nerve to crop type and color to the edge — to let one bold
          field carry a whole page — is <strong>Reid Miles</strong> at Blue Note. And the
          discipline of black, white, and a single color that doesn't ask permission is
          <strong>Massimo Vignelli's</strong>, by way of the Unigrid.
        </p>
        <p>
          The case for the working journal — over the portfolio, over the case-study deck,
          over the LinkedIn — comes from <strong>Frank Chimero</strong>, <strong>Robin
          Sloan</strong>, and the body of long-form writing that quietly insists the personal
          site is still the right primitive. <em>It is.</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          The <strong>Archivo</strong> family was developed by Omnibus Type. It's open-source,
          and responsible for whatever this site reads as.
        </p>
        <p>
          And to the reader who got to the bottom of the colophon: <em>thank you for
          looking.</em> You are why the site is here. <a href="/ink">Here's something fun and beautiful, just for you.</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="stamp-row">
      <span class="stamp">Last revised Q2 2026 · Updated quarterly · Brandon E. B. Ward · Dallas</span>
      <span class="fleuron" aria-hidden="true">❦</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
